Class Filter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Filter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - a type of object
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericFilter<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompareFilter, FilterCascade, FilterN, IdentityFilter, ScalarFilter

    public abstract class Filter<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements GenericFilter<T>
    Filter is an abstract class that implements GenericFilter. It sets up the general outline for how a filter works: it processes an input, and returns the local output.
